# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# __xor__ dict-presence — operator.contains(Cls.__dict__, '__xor__')
#
# All 10 asyncio classes return false for __xor__.
# Bitwise XOR (^) is defined for integers (bit-flip) and sets (symmetric
#   difference). asyncio types are neither integer types nor set-like
#   collections.
# asyncio.Event: a boolean flag managed by set()/clear()/wait(); ^ is
#   not defined for event state XOR.
# asyncio.Lock/Condition: mutex and condition variable abstractions; no
#   XOR semantics exist for lock composition.
# asyncio.Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore: permit-counter types; the counter
#   is entirely encapsulated — no bitwise XOR is exposed.
# asyncio.Task/Future: pending coroutine results; ^ is undefined for tasks.
# asyncio.Queue/PriorityQueue/LifoQueue: container types with no
#   set-algebra protocol; ^ (symmetric difference) is not defined.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

